<h3>The SXO Score Framework</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="SXO score framework showing visibility, experience, and conversion weights" src="/images/blog/sxo-score-framework.webp" /></p>
<p>Create a composite score for each page:</p>
<p><strong>SXO Score = (Visibility Score × 0.3) + (Experience Score × 0.4) + (Conversion Score × 0.3)</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Visibility Score (0 to 100):</strong> Based on ranking position and organic traffic vs. target</li>
<li><strong>Experience Score (0 to 100):</strong> Based on Core Web Vitals pass rate, bounce rate, and time on page</li>
<li><strong>Conversion Score (0 to 100):</strong> Based on goal completion rate vs. benchmark</li>
</ul>
<p>Weight experience highest because it drives both ranking improvements and conversion improvements. A page that scores high on experience will naturally improve its visibility and conversion scores over time.</p>
